\cf2\b There are 2 significant changes\b0  in this version of PTXprint which you need to be aware of:\cf0\par
\par
\cf3 (1) Changes have been made to the underlying XeTeX macros which will improve the layout of the text, particularly footnotes. However, these \b minor changes could cause the text to flow differently\b0 , which is not ideal if you are part way through a typesetting project. To help maintain backward compatibility, a system has been introduced which enables you to Lock the XeTeX Layout engine to a previous level. So if you need to revert to the previous XeTeX layout then take the following steps:\cf0\par
\cf3       (a) Enable the option (on the Advanced tab) \f1\ldblquote\f0 Lock XeTeX Layout Level\f1\rdblquote\cf0\f0\par
\cf3       (b) Enable the option \f1\ldblquote\f0 Show TeXpert Hacks\f1\rdblquote\cf0\f0\par
\cf3       (c) Switch to the \f1\ldblquote\f0 TeXpert Hacks\f1\rdblquote\f0  tab\cf0\par
\cf3       (d) Set the \f1\ldblquote\b\f0 Maximum Layout Version\b0\f1\rdblquote\f0  to \b 1\b0  (down from 2) at top of list (0=latest)\cf0\par
\cf3 Doing this should cause the text to flow exactly as it was in previous versions (pre 2.5).\cf0\par
\par
\cf4 (2) In order to keep up with underlying software changes (Python 3.11+) \b Regular Expressions are now stricter\b0 . You must \f1\lquote\f0 escape\f1\rquote\f0  any \\ backslash codes with an additional \\ in your changes.txt rules. So for example, a rule like:\cf0\par
\cf4     \cf2 "\\p" > "\\m"\cf4  will need to be \f1\lquote\f0 fixed\f1\rquote\f0 :  \cf2 "{\cf0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "\\\\\\\\p"}}{\fldrslt{\\\\p\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20 " > "{\cf0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "\\\\\\\\m"}}{\fldrslt{\\\\m\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20 "\cf0\par
\cf4 But notice that you only need to add the \\ to escape \b USFM codes\b0 , not all the other valid codes like \\r \\n \\1 \\2 and so on:\cf0\par
\cf4     \cf6 "({\cf0\b{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "\\\\\\\\id"}}{\fldrslt{\\\\id\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20  (...).*\\n)" > "\\1{\b{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "\\\\\\\\h1 \\\\2\\\\r\\\\n"}}{\fldrslt{\\\\h1\b0  \\2\\r\\n\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20 "\par
