\b "Bible Layout For Everyone"\b0  - Easily create scripture PDFs for trial publications\par
\par
PTXprint is an easy-to-use program which harnesses the power of extended macros from PTX2PDF which is a XeTeX based macro package for typesetting USFM formatted (Paratext) scripture files.\par
\par
PTXprint is available for both Linux and Windows from the main home page: {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://software.sil.org/ptxprint/download }}{\fldrslt{https://software.sil.org/ptxprint/download\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20  \par
It is 64-bit software and will NOT run on 32-bit versions of Windows. It is recommended to be used with Paratext 9.x (or later), but can also work even if Paratext is NOT installed. It is not part of the Paratext updates ecosystem, so does not get automatically updated. Please check the PTXprint home page regularly for updated versions.\par
\par
There is a category dedicated to PTXprint issues on ({{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://support.bible/PTXprint }}{\fldrslt{https://support.bible/PTXprint\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20 ) where you can get assistance from other PTXprint users.\par
\par
Please use "New Issue" button in the GitHub Issue Tracking System ({{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://github.com/sillsdev/ptx2pdf/issues }}{\fldrslt{https://github.com/sillsdev/ptx2pdf/issues\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20 ) to report any bugs, or document suggestions for improvement. \par
\par
If you serve in a sensitive location, you can report issues directly by e-mail <{{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "mailto:ptxprint_support@sil.org" }}{\fldrslt{\ul\cf5\cf7\ul ptxprint_support@sil.org}}}}\f0\fs20 > rather than via the publicly accessible websites listed above.\par
\par
\par
\b\fs22 Examples of running PTXprint from the command-line (in Windows):\b0\fs20\par
\par
\cf2 "C:\\Program Files\\PTXprint\\PTXprint.exe" -c Diglot XYZ\cf0\par
will OPEN PTXprint with XYZ project active and the saved configuration called "Diglot" (but won't print anything)\par
\par
\cf2 "C:\\Program Files\\PTXprint\\PTXprint.exe" -c NTandPsalms -P XYZ\cf0\par
will directly create a PDF from the XYZ project using the saved configuration called "NTandPsalms" (no GUI will appear)\par
\par
\cf2 "C:\\Program Files\\PTXprint\\PTXprint.exe" -b ROM -c SideXrefs -P XYZ\cf0\par
will directly create a PDF of ROMANS from the XYZ project using the saved configuration called "SideXrefs" (no GUI will appear)\par
\par
\cf2 "C:\\Program Files\\PTXprint\\PTXprint.exe" -b "MAT MRK LUK JHN ACT GLO" -P XYZ\cf0\par
will directly create a PDF of 4 gospels, Acts and Glossary from the XYZ project using the Default configuration (no GUI will appear)\par
\par
\cf2 "C:\\Program Files\\PTXprint\\PTXprint.exe" -p C:\\Data\\VariousUSFMprojects\cf0\par
with -p (lowercase) and a folder name will run PTXprint pointing to that folder instead of the usual Paratext folder. Note that\par
it expects one or more subfolders which contain the actual USFM files. The names of any subfolders containing valid .SFM files\par
will appear in the Project drop-down menu once PTXprint has opened.\par
\par
\cf2 "C:\\Program Files\\PTXprint\\PTXprint.exe" -d "C:\\Temp"\cf0\par
runs PTXprint, and output PDF files will be created in C:\\Temp folder instead of C:\\My Paratext 9 Projects\\<XYZ>\\local\\ptxprint\par
